About the Dish
This bottle gourd raita is special to me because it turns a humble everyday vegetable into something comforting, flavorful, and refreshing. The tiny chopped pieces of lauki soak up the aroma of mustard seeds, cumin, curry leaves, and red chillies, giving every bite a warm South Indian touch. Mixed into cool, creamy curd with just the right amount of salt, it becomes a simple homemade dish that feels light, nourishing, and deeply satisfying. It’s the kind of recipe that proves comfort food doesn’t need to be complicated.



Ingredients
1 small bottle gourd (lauki / sorakaya), finely chopped
1 cup curd (yogurt), whisked
Salt to taste
For Tempering
1 tsp mustard seeds
1 tsp cumin seeds
1–2 dried red chillies
A few curry leaves
1 tsp oil

Method
Heat oil in a pan.
Add mustard seeds and let them splutter.
Add cumin seeds, dried red chillies, and curry leaves.
Add finely chopped bottle gourd pieces and sauté until soft and cooked.
Let the bottle gourd cool slightly.
Add it to the whisked curd.
Add salt to taste and mix well.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.

  
Optional Additions
Chopped coriander leaves
Green chilli for extra spice
